132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1493
S.P. 608 In Senate, April 8, 2025
An Act to Eliminate Tax and Wage Incentives for Visual Media
Production Companies
Reference to the Committee on Taxation suggested and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator TIPPING of Penobscot.
Cosponsored by Representative MATLACK of St. George and
Senator: TEPLER of Sagadahoc, Representatives: GOLEK of Harpswell, LOOKNER of
Portland, RANA of Bangor.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 5 MRSA §13090-L, as amended by PL 2011, c. 285, §1, is repealed.
3 Sec. 2. 10 MRSA §1100-T, sub-§2, ¶B, as amended by PL 2013, c. 438, §3, is
4 further amended to read:
5 B. The Maine business must be determined by the authority to be a manufacturer or a
6 value-added natural resource enterprise; must provide a product or service that is sold
7 or rendered, or is projected to be sold or rendered, predominantly outside of the State;
8 or must be engaged in the development or application of advanced technologies; or
9 must be certified as a visual media production company under Title 5, section 13090‑L.
10 The business must certify that the amount of the investment is necessary to allow the
11 business to create or retain jobs in the State.
12 Sec. 3. 10 MRSA §1100-T, sub-§2-A, ¶B, as amended by PL 2019, c. 616, Pt.
13 LL, §4, is further amended to read:
14 B. As used in this subsection, unless the context otherwise indicates, an "eligible
15 business" means a business located in the State that:
16 (1) Is a manufacturer;
17 (2) Is engaged in the development or application of advanced technologies;
18 (3) Provides a product or service that is sold or rendered, or is projected to be sold
19 or rendered, predominantly outside of the State; or
20 (4) Brings capital into the State, as determined by the authority; or.
21 (5) Is certified as a visual media production company under Title 5, section
22 13090‑L.
23 Sec. 4. 10 MRSA §1100-T, sub-§2-C, ¶B, as amended by PL 2019, c. 616, Pt.
24 LL, §6, is further amended to read:
25 B. As used in this subsection, unless the context otherwise indicates, "eligible
26 business" means a business located in the State that has certified that the amount of the
27 investment is necessary to allow the business to create or retain jobs in the State and
28 that, as determined by the authority:
29 (1) Is a manufacturer or a value-added natural resource enterprise;
30 (2) Is engaged in the development or application of advanced technologies; or
31 (3) Provides a product or service that is sold or rendered, or is projected to be sold
32 or rendered, predominantly outside of the State; or.
33 (5) Is certified as a visual media production company under Title 5, section
34 13090‑L.
35 Sec. 5. 36 MRSA §191, sub-§2, ¶MM, as amended by PL 2009, c. 652, Pt. A,
36 §51, is further amended to read:
37 MM. The disclosure to an authorized representative of the Department of Economic
38 and Community Development of information required for the administration of the
39 visual media production credit under section 5219‑Y, the employment tax increment
40 financing program under chapter 917, the visual media production reimbursement
Page 1 - 132LR1865(01)

411 program under chapter 919‑A or the Pine Tree Development Zone program under Title
422 30‑A, chapter 206, subchapter 4;
3 Sec. 6. 36 MRSA §5219-Y, as amended by PL 2011, c. 240, §37, is repealed.
4 Sec. 7. 36 MRSA c. 919-A, as amended, is repealed.
5 SUMMARY
66 This bill repeals the provisions of law governing certified visual media production
77 credits and visual media production reimbursements. It also makes corresponding changes
88 necessitated by the repeal of those provisions.
